==English==

===Etymology===
From [[over-]] + [[expose]] + [[-ed]]

===Adjective===
'''overexposed'''
# [[exposed|Exposed]] too much, especially of [[film]] or a [[photograph]].
#:''The snapshot was '''overexposed''', giving its subjects a too-bright, washed out appearance.''

